<plot>Once upon a time there was a young boy who wanted to be a filmmaker. Things were going well for this talented young artist until his older brother, a struggling filmmaker in his own right, decided to do everything in his power to steal his brother's film and make it his own. Such is the tale in Laurence N. Kaldor's directorial debut, Directing Eddie - a light-hearted "feel-good" romantic comedy about sibling rivalry, set in the backdrop of the independent film world.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?151015</url></doc>
